                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports the passage, by large majority, of meat-inspection bill in
                    exceedingly severe form, and that the Government opposition appeared not to be
                    very earnest. The bill will now go to the Imperial Council, where it will
                    probably be somewhat modified.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
